<li id="cite_note-183"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-183">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Bakhtin, Mikhail 1981. <i>The Dialogic Imagination.</i> Austin, TX: UT Press, p.4</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-184"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-184">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Lindlof &amp; Taylor, 2002,p.60</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-185"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-185">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">O'Neil, D. 2006. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://anthro.palomar.edu/change/change_2.htm">"Processes of Change"</a>.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-186"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-186">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Pringle, H. 1998. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://cas.bellarmine.edu/tietjen/images/neolithic_agriculture.htm">The Slow Birth of Agriculture</a>. <i>Science</i> 282: 1446.</span></li>
</ol>
